Food for children suffering from obesity: No breakfast and cabbage for dinner
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 are more weight than normal; while 9% of schoolchildren are overweight, 5% suffer from obesity.
According to the latest study, children suffering from obesity usually come from families leading an unhealthy lifestyle.
We see again the importance of the environment and behavior patterns that accompany a person for his or her healthy development.
For example, cabbage appears on the tables of children suffering from obesity almost twice as often as in families with children with normal weight.
More than 19% of children suffering from obesity eat for dinner free potatoes on the eve of the survey relating to an educational event called Obesity is not a coincidence.
Moreover, the families of children suffering from obesity do not do sports. This, however, applies to the majority of the families of modern schoolchildren - only 15% of children said their parents find time to do sports at least once a week.
The study was conducted among 900 children.
The study was conducted at the end of last academic year; it attended 900 primary class students throughout Bohemia.
This event was held for the second year in a row, with the support of the insurance company Všeobecná zdravotní pojišťovna and Unilever.
At the present time, more than 12,000 students from 4 to 8 classes have joined the project.
Correct nutrition and adequate sports loads are the main determining factors that cause a rapidly growing number of children suffering either from excess weight or obesity.
“For example, only half of the respondents said they ate five times a day, according to the scheme of breakfast, breakfast, lunch, dinner, and that’s one of the indispensable conditions for proper nutrition,” one of the findings said.
No clay and clay in the evening.
Experts warn that even such relative details are important for healthy development, such as the constant time of family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of schoolchildren’s families eat breakfast together.
Most families eat breakfast separately.
The worst discovery was that in every ten families people don’t eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis for the right daily diet.
Research has shown that cooked food is more common in families with children suffering from obesity.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet cooling drinks every day (70%).
Although more than 40% of children regularly do sports, this figure decreases more than twice - to 15% - when it comes to their parents.
Create your own menu.
In the second part of the study, selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) were suggested to make their own menu based on the products offered and based on their own tastes and preferences.
“The food preferences in Czech children aged 12-15 years are far from the ideal in terms of healthy eating.”
Their favorite food includes a large amount of flour, meat and sweet dishes.
"Special concern is caused by the great popularity of sweet cooling drinks," the study says in the final part.
As the main meal, the pasta defeated the bird with a small overweight.
However, children practically showed no interest in beans, fish and vegetable dishes.
Desire for a healthy way of life
The study also showed that children are ready to change their eating habits provided they are provided with relevant information.
"Many participants in the study control group demonstrated a significant shift in preferences towards healthy food when they filled up the questionnaire after the conclusion of the lesson Obesity is not a coincidence," the project said.
This was noticeable, for example, in the case of sweet cooling drinks - more children began to prefer them just water.
Additionally, as the main dish, children were more likely to note the bird and fish, limiting the amount of sweet dishes and bakes.
