Need for Speed: Escape takes place in America.
Review
What had to be a careless walk turned into a routine morning trip to work due to a series of completely inappropriate and negligent errors.
Ambitions to a certain extent were satisfied, but it doesn’t matter, as no one clearly wanted to do an extra job.
Before the release with the new version with the subtitle "Flying" linked great hopes.
It was expected that it would move the previous series of Need For Speed in a new direction; the demonstration versions showed that the game will take a decent place in the race game genre.
We were curious to see parts of the game where the main character comes out of the car and runs.
As it often happens with NFS, there is a lot different from what we expected.
The game is a pretty bad arcade race, but the overall impression is broken by a few unnecessary errors that are present in this series of games for several years.
And thus, in reality, this is not a mistake, but a manifestation of the unexplicable line of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You’re becoming part of a story whose protagonist, Jack, decides to solve some personal problems by participating in an illegal race through America.
You’re sitting in a car on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your task is to get first to New York.
This idea has a few interesting features.
The route consists of ten stages, divided into more than fifty races.
This means that each race goes on its own route, the individual stages go in a diverse and interesting environment.
There is no feeling that the same thing happens all the time in the game.
Despite the fact that the graph is at the same level as in the previous parts of the series, some trails are pleasant to watch.
However, the game does not cause strong emotions.
Although driving the car through the desert, through the autumn suburbs or high in the snowed mountains is very pleasant.
Furthermore, the race from time to time revives an unusual detail.
For example, in the desert you get into a sandy storm that significantly decreases the visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you need to be careful not to fall under the labyrinth.
The races are quite well arranged.
There are only a few varieties, but that is enough.
For some time you’re trying to overcome several rivals (in essence a regular race); then you’re trying to improve the time (standard race with a second meter); or you’re competing with one opponent.
On the other hand, you’re getting to the police from time to time, which makes your task even more complicated.
The components outside of the car are new.
It’s just an interactive animation where most of the time Jack escapes from someone and you have to help him by pressing the right buttons at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
Although it’s surprising that these fragments are much less than you could expect (all three to be accurate).
In fact, it turns out that it’s good for the game because this property is not tired; taking into account all the above, it’s one of the things that make the game more interesting.
The race model follows the traces of the previous models.
This means that it is no longer something special, but it cannot be considered a disadvantage.
If you’re looking for a real life imitation, you’ll have to look elsewhere.
And yet this model of driving is very suitable for dynamic races, although better options can be found on the market.
So far everything is very well.
However, after a while the problems begin.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not so good.
From such a game you don’t expect complicated transformations and collisions, but if you don’t have any idea before you collide with the object, how your machine will behave, something is wrong.
Usually, riding or passing through the cars in a narrow stream, you are sometimes slightly touched by another car. And yet sometimes in a practically similar situation your car begins to rush.
Or suddenly broken.
This is not so important thanks to the restart system, but this is enough to break the fun.
The rebounds are arranged so that if you break down or go far from the track, the game returns you to the point where it was interrupted.
There are only five rebounds available for each race.
If you use them all, you will have to start the race from the beginning.
This is useful if something fails, but you can’t fully rely on it.
Sometimes rebounds are not enough, and you have to learn the separate area of the race.
An important disadvantage of the game is the fact that the same things often happen in the same places.
For example, some turns need to pass in a certain way, otherwise you simply won’t fit.
In other cases, you meet civil cars in a specific place in the same configuration regardless of whether you arrive first, fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is annoying in situations when you see how your opponent easily passes between two cars moving in the opposite direction, while when you are there, the cars are already located so that you need either to run them or drop the speed.
It doesn’t matter when you’re next to them; everything is arranged so that the situation always happens just before your nose.
The competitors have other advantages.
During the game you will find several places where, regardless of the time, the same opponent pursues you in the same place.
This is obvious at the end of the game, on a long bridge where you’re going in the opposite direction.
Obviously, your rival must stand up before you despite anything.
The fact is that when he goes before you, he worsenes your view, which leads to one or more accidents in this area.
You can understand the attempt to make the game more interesting and filled with adrenaline, but it’s so obvious that it quickly begins to cause irritation.
Sadly because despite the simple model of driving, the game is fun and sometimes so saturated with events that you don’t have time to pay attention to what’s happening around you.
It doesn’t matter what doesn’t miss you – a concept with fifty unique trails, a sequence of races or something else.
The idea of changing cars during the race is unusual.
You need to track the supplies on the road because it is on them your car can change, despite the fact that in most cases the one you already have is quite enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for cities; powerful U.S. cars are suitable for direct road cuts; and exotic super-sport cars are suitable for technical driving, for example, on rough mountain trails.
The main story mode is closely linked to the challenge mode; it’s races on individual areas that you’ll learn during the game.
Here you win for your personal business both medals and glasses, common for challenges and story modes.
Many options are available to get a higher driving level: starting from machines and ending with profile data.
In addition, the profile is linked to the online Autolog feature, which, among all other things, compares the results you have achieved with the results of other players, and provides communication with the public.
Here is another disadvantage that is difficult to understand; this is an example from the last race in a sequence.
You and your car get into the metro tunnel (we'll think that's so), where you're swallowing on the rails in the dark (we'll think that's so).
Your spidometer shows figures from 150 to 200 km/h (we’ll think that’s so) when suddenly a subway train runs on your back, turning your car into a metal thumb.
For a few days, our edition discussed whether at the time of creating the game no one thought for a second, or its creators really considered us such a bull.
The technical component of the game is nothing special; but the overall impression from the video game is mostly pleasant, sometimes even stunning.
Although it is unfortunate that at some critical moments the quality of recording, sometimes quite strongly, decreases.
This especially applies to accidents with a large number of participants, where a good record would not help you too.
Sound is in order; soundtrack is for the lover.
In order to satisfy the wider youth audience as possible, the soundtrack's compositions of different styles came in; but it's unlikely that many people buy the game because of its music.
The overall impression of Need for Speed: Escape is quite uncommon.
If the game avoided obviously unnecessary errors, we could honestly say that Escape is the best part of NFS in the past few years.
Anyway, the game leaves the feeling of incomplete.
Of course, it’s a good entertainment, but be prepared for the fact that the shortcomings will blind you as a airport lighting.
The people of Karlov University will perform at the concert "Students in Barhat"
The third year in a row festival Festa Academia offers to combine the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Barhat Revolution with a musical event.
It will present about twenty school and university chores.
The main event of the festival is two concerts that will take place on November 17.
“Carlov University is taking an active participation in the festival.”
“The participants include the Hor of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities; Vaclav Gample, rector, will enter the committee,” said Jacob Chalun, head of the organizational committee.
The culmination will be a free public concert of the school chores, which will take place at 2 p.m. on November 17 at the square in front of the National Technical Library in Davis.
The work "Jazz Mass", the composition of the famous Czech jazzman, Karela Ružička, is also included in the program.
In the evening, in the official National House in Vinograd will be held a concert "Students in the Barhat", with the participation of the university chores, including the chores of the University of Karlov.
The objective of Festa Academica is to celebrate the International Student Day and honorably celebrate the 22nd anniversary of the Barhat Revolution; as well as to present to the public the music of the highest quality and to develop creative interaction among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech pěveckých sborů (Czech chorus) in cooperation with the secondary school named Johann Kepler.
The whole event takes place with the help of Boguslav Freedom, Lord Mayor of Prague, and Vaclav Gampla, Rector of the Karlov University.
The festival will take place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program offers both official concerts and numerous musical meetings, student hopping, daily performances, etc.
For more information please contact the festival’s website: www.festaacademica.cz
