The decline of economic activity caused, until November, the constant growth of unemployment in the state, according to the National Institute of Statistics and Geography, during the first three quarters was recorded accelerated growth of unemployment, from January to March 55.053 inhabitants of Sinaloa were unemployed, with a share of 4.53 per cent of the economically active population, in the second quarter the share increased to 5.28 per cent, and from July to September it continued to grow to 6.19 per cent, the share, which in the number of people is more than 74.000 unemployed in Sinaloa, which is 18.969 per cent more than the first half.
Reduction of liquidity
Unemployment in Sinaloa during the year discussed by many factors, for the economist Gerardo Lopez Cervantes, director of the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the Autonomous University (UAS), the growth of unemployment can be explained indirectly, by the actions that took place in public policy.
“What we see now is an increase in unemployment that is associated with several factors, including the loss of liquidity on the market in order to limit the resources imposed by the law, which was adopted in Congress to fight money laundering, as people who illegally own dollars are not easy to work with them, invest and use them in something,” he said.
suspended immigration
Lopez Cervantes said that there is also a demographic factor in the growth of unemployment.
