The average monthly income of the workers of Sinaloa was until September 5,352 pesos, much below the country average, which is 7,375 pesos.
Reduction of PI
In addition to the decline in economic activity and the high rate of unemployment in 2011 was recorded the largest flow of foreign direct investments in the last 10 years, according to the Ministry of Finance, from January to July the state’s PII was $630.697 which shows a decline of 87.74 percent compared to $5.143.312 during the same period last year.
