The replacement of analog signals with digital signals is one of the most important changes that the world has achieved in recent years.
The Supreme Court rejected the constitutional claims made by the Senate and the House of Representatives against the presidential decree, which carries the so-called "transition to digital television" from 2021 to 2015, since the eight votes were not collected necessary for its cancellation.
