Only El Salvador, Jorge Mario Pardo, Margarita Luna and Sanchez Cordero voted for the project.
According to this argument, both the Senate and the House of Representatives conducted two constitutional trials to deny the decree and support complaints, Minister Sanchez Cordero suspended the application of the decree and all the actions mentioned in it regarding the transition to digital broadcasting.
