"I also don't think that if this happened, it would affect the autonomy of the regulatory body," and reminded that the planning of state policy in strategic areas, such as the telecommunications sector, is related to the federal executive authority, which has a constitutional mandate, governance by the state.
The replacement of analog signals for digital is one of the most important changes that have occurred in recent years, resulting in better use of the radio spectrum, better quality of the signal and more channels.
