In Michoacan, we analyze the possibility of counting "voice for voice"
According to the data transmitted to the PPRV, the difference between the first and second places in the governor's elections is just 27 percent, even without counting the votes, coming to 879 out of the total number in 6.074 protocols.
The possibility of counting "vote by vote" is real as regards the election process this year in Michoacan, where, according to the data obtained from the Program for Pre-Voting Results (PPRV), the difference between the first and second places in the governor's elections is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes coming to 879 out of the total number in 6.074 protocols.
In light of this, the Chairman of the General Council of the Michoacan Election Institute (IMM), Maria de Los Angeles Lianderal Zaragoza, reminded that a few days ago, November 9, the electoral body approved a package of principles to harmonize local rules with the federal electoral reform.
As it should be remembered, Michoacan did not accept the Constitution or the State Electoral Code or the Electoral Law, as the State Congress approved the reforms shortly before the legitimate deadline of their entry into force in this election process and Governor Leonel Gody Rangel did not include its publication within the deadlines specified in the law in the Official Gazette of the State, stating that he has some objections.
On the same day, 9 November, the Supreme Court of Justice (High Court of Justice) adopted a decision on the constitutional claim made by the local legislative assembly, and called the vote of a representative of the state on the constitutional reform "invalid and illegal" because he has no right to "accept or support them."
In an interview on the possibility of "vote by vote" Maria de los Angeles Lianderal stated that with the adoption of the appropriate principles by the General Council of the IMM will be possible to submit a partial or full number of votes by the local electoral body.
So, a partial recalculation of one or more voting urns can be made under the conditions that: the results of the protocols do not match; there is no voting and accounting protocol in the urn or it is not in the presidential office; or when there are obvious errors or corrections in the protocol.
Furthermore, the total number of votes in all urns at the elections may take place when there is a sign that the difference between the supposed candidate-winner of the elections in question and the one who won the second place in voting is less or equal to one percentage, provided that at the beginning of the session there is a request from a representative of the party and/or coalition that presented the second of the mentioned candidates.
A total number of votes shall also be made if at the end of the ordinary number is stated that the difference between the winner and the second-place candidate is less or equal to one percentage, provided that there is a request from the political party whose candidate has second-place candidate, in the event that the electoral urns that were taken into account at the partial number are excluded.
It is worth noting that in this situation are elections in Morelia, where, according to the PPRV, the difference between the first and second places is only 0.16 percent, even without counting 129 votes from the total number in 923 protocols.
